metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of François Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl

metadata.name: Make-believe #4
metadata.description:
#genuary32nd – Let's meet on this make-believe date, in this make-believe place.
I’m having déjà vu, or is it a memory?

metadata.name: Kink #189
metadata.description:
Kink is a representation of the idea that creative evolution is born from the subtle twists, turns, and kinks. 

A base element is manipulated, bent and reshaped, subjecting it to the artistic equivalent of a kink. When several such ideas converge, they give birth to a fresh concept altogether through an evolution in thought and form.

Implemented in JS, this code utilizes the Perlin.js and Simple-noise.js libraries.

Press p to save a PNG of the image in full screen. Press s to save a single complete SVG file for plotting.

And this is a redeemable project in case you’d like to receive a physical plot!

Pixel Love!

metadata.name: Sketches:Pairs of Tails:Majestic Creatures #29
metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.

metadata.name: Angular Variations (Holding Space) #61
metadata.description:
Angular Variations. Holding space for transitions. Once minted the lines maintain their design while the spaces between adjust to accommodate changes in canvas size.

There are no rarity attributes assigned to this artwork, its value is intended to be determined by viewer aesthetic alone.

This artwork was created using p5js.

twitter: @lisaorthstudio

metadata.name: odium #47
metadata.description:
The idea behind "odium" is to mix the two previous works to create a new art, which maintains similarities with the previous projects, but also with its differences and peculiarities.

"odium" is based on an algorithm that I've been exploring since the "radium" and "illusions" projects. So this is the last of the series.

It is composed by with grainy/noise and flowfields, creating a glitch effect as it is finishing to render.
"odium" have random colormaps instead a configured palette system, patterns of growth and plays with randomized blendModes and colorModes, 
and I name it "odium"  because the form it grows and glitch reminds me how the hate sometimes slowly consume the mind.

This is a project made in p5.js


Omar Lobato, 04/29/2022.

metadata.name: 生成畫荷 #36
metadata.description:
It ain't hard to tell, code compiles, and then art reveals.

「天一生水，地六成之；地二生火，天七成之；天三生木，地八成之；地四生金，天九成之；天五生土，地十成之。天生地成，而行鬼神。」— 河圖

Heaven gens, earth erates, the acts of demons and gods, indefinitely, generate. 

荷花一現，河圖不見，生花成畫，心幸有憐。

I see that lotus, but this code does not render it. Flowers are generative, art is generative, and we feel. 

「自抒胸意，不襲前人；無人無我，無古無今」— 張大千七十七歲作

There is no I nor they, past or present. — Zhang Da Qian~1976

「墨落一時手不住，任譏老子做狂徒。」— 張大千八十四歲作

Oops! ink fell out of my hand. But, I, got it.  — Zhang Da Qian~1983

“We see things in things, 
then create and drop,
copyminters only look at commits, 
on github. 
Though they need not to peek,
my gen art’s free, to see, 
stuff on my mind, 
do not like, to be locked, in a file, 
it ain’t hard to smell.” — Zhang Da Qian x Nas x Jimi Wen

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

4’33’” - a 3-movement composition by experimental composer John Cage. 

4’33” - THE MUSIC.  Cage wrote the score instructing performers not to play their instruments during the entire duration of the piece. Though it is often perceived as silence, it is in that context: the sounds of the environment, being that, it becomes music.  

4’33” - fx(hash) gentk, you get a flatpack stained glass tea hut. Your tea hut, prefabbed with fixed geometry and fixed color palette straight out of the box. 

The code interprets your hash as pertaining to where and how you build this hut. Though it might look like noise or glitch, it is in the context: the light in us colors the shadows, reflections, celebrations of life, and acts in life.  

If you listen c a . r .    e .    f .      u .     l .        l.        y you can hear the reverberation, sounds of splendid joy in it. 

p5.js may take about 4.33 seconds to draw. Press 1 to save png.
